rider55 .</a></h4><p class="author"><span class="asked-ago">Asked <time class="submission-date" title="Feb 25, 2020 6:16 PM">7 months ago</time> by<!-- --> <!-- -->Lowrider55<!-- -->.</span></p><ul class="answers"><li class="answer"><div class="answer-text" data-answer-id="e04c2a6e-3f48-353a-8c62-98723539d0b5" id="answer-id-e04c2a6e-3f48-353a-8c62-98723539d0b5" tabindex="-1"><div class="ugc-components line-clamp"><div class="undefined fade-out "><span aria-hidden="true" class="v-fw-medium">A:</span><span class="sr-only">Answer</span> <span>If Fortnight on PC allows controller play (I don't know, I don't play Fortnite) then the answer is Yes. The controller is Bluetooth and compatible with Windows, MacOS, Nintendo Switch and Android (and likely anything else that takes a Bluetooth signal). It also has charging cord that can hardwire it to devices that don't have Bluetooth. If you have an Xbox One S or later or a Playstation 4, you should try using those with your PC since they're both Bluetooth and may likely work.</span></div><button class="btn btn-link v-medium btn-read-more read-more-button" type="button" data-track="QnA: Answer: Read More" aria-describedby="e04c2a6e-3f48-353a-8c62-98723539d0b5" href="">Read more <svg aria-hidden="true" role="img" viewBox="0 0 100 100"><use href="/~assets/bby/_img/int/plsvgdef-frontend/svg/Caret_Down_Line_Sm.svg#Caret_Down_Line_Sm" xlink:href="/~assets/bby/_img/int/plsvgdef-frontend/svg/Caret_Down_Line_Sm.svg#Caret_Down_Line_Sm"></use></svg></button></div></div><p class="author">Answered <time class="submission-date" title="Mar 1, 2020 10:11 AM">7 months ago</time> by<!-- --> <!-- -->citizenjames<span class="c-overlay-wrapper"><span class="overlayTrigger"><button class="btn btn-link v-medium ugc-components verified-purchaser-badge" type="button" data-track="QnA: Badge: Verified Purchase" href="" aria-expanded="false" aria-controls="verified-purchase-badge-overlay" aria-describedby="verified-purchase-badge-overlay"><img alt="" aria